# AIOS Architecture Rules

## LLM Access

- ALL LLM calls go through `ai/AIGatewayService` — never inject `ChatModel` outside `ai/`
- Controllers and `ChatService` must not call Spring AI directly

## Package Boundaries

| Package | Responsibility |
|---------|---------------|
| `gateway/` | Filters, rate limiting — no business logic |
| `ai/` | Firewall, routing, execution, audit — no REST or JPA |
| `chat/` | Conversations, messages, chat API — no direct LLM calls |
| `memory/` | Context orchestration — no chat persistence |
| `auth/` | Security only |
| `common/` | Shared DTOs, exceptions — no domain logic |
| `config/` | Spring beans — no feature code |

## Data & Schema

- Schema changes → Flyway migration in `db/migration/`, never `ddl-auto: update`
- JPA entities live in `chat/entity/`
- `@Transactional` belongs on service classes, not controllers

## API Conventions

- All endpoints under `/api/v1/`
- Responses use `ApiResponse<T>` or `ApiErrorResponse`
- Chat endpoints require authentication

## Logging

- NEVER log prompt text, response content, or API keys
- Audit logs: metadata only (model, latency, tokens, conversationId)
